Analysis: Wait, I found a potential race condition in `unpin()`. 
```java
        int remaining = pins.decrementAndGet();
        if (remaining == 0 && cooled.get()) {
            closeLoadedGeneration();
        }
```
If `pins.decrementAndGet()` brings `remaining` to 0, but `cooled.get()` is still false, then `closeLoadedGeneration()` is not called. If another thread then calls `cool()`, it will call `unpin()`, which will bring `pins` to -1 and throw an exception! Wait, no, because `cool()` only calls `unpin()` if it successfully set `cooled` from false to true. If `cooled` was already true, it wouldn't call `unpin()`. But if `unpin()` was called first and brought `pins` to 0, and then `cool()` was called, it would call `unpin()` again, bringing `pins` to -1.
Plan: I should fix the logic in `unpin()` and `cool()` to ensure `closeLoadedGeneration()` is called exactly once when both conditions are met, without underflowing the pins.

